# Browser executable paths used by index.js.
# Copy this file to browser-paths.properties and update paths for your machine.
# On Windows, browser-installer/download-browsers.ps1 refreshes managed browser
# paths automatically unless you pass -NoBrowserPaths.
# Multiple candidates per key can be separated with semicolons.
# Windows environment variables in %VAR% form are expanded automatically.

# --- Windows examples ---
opera=%LOCALAPPDATA%\Programs\Opera\opera.exe
comet=%LOCALAPPDATA%\Perplexity\Comet\Application\comet.exe
duckduckgo=%LOCALAPPDATA%\Microsoft\WindowsApps\DuckDuckGo.exe

# --- macOS examples (uncomment if on Mac) ---
# opera=/Applications/Opera.app/Contents/MacOS/Opera
# comet=/Applications/Comet.app/Contents/MacOS/Comet
# duckduckgo=/Applications/DuckDuckGo.app/Contents/MacOS/DuckDuckGo
# atlas=/Applications/ChatGPT Atlas.app/Contents/MacOS/ChatGPT Atlas;/Applications/Atlas.app/Contents/MacOS/Atlas

# --- Notes ---
# safari/webkit: use --browser webkit; no path needed, Playwright bundles a WebKit engine.
# safari on macOS only: use --browser safari (requires Safari Technology Preview or system Safari).
# atlas: ChatGPT Atlas is currently macOS-only.
